The 2006 [[Widnes Vikings]] season was their first in the [[2006 Rugby League National Leagues]] since their relegation from the [[Super League]] the previous season. The Widnes Vikings aimed for immediate promotion back to the top tier eventually finishing second in the league and making it to the Grand Final. They ultimately fell short of this goal being defeated by [[Hull Kingston Rovers]] by 29 points to 16.<ref name="Hull KR 29-16 Widnes">{{cite news|title=Hull KR 29-16 Widnes|url=https://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/rugby_league/5412522.stm|access-date=16 August 2017|agency=BBC|publisher=BBC Sport|date=8 October 2006|ref=1}}</ref>

